task.summary: Default task
My wife fixed (again) my IN statement for TE and WR players
Update TE query for AFC

Update reset password and welcome email template
Reset password is not working - always code not found. Will need to troubleshoot. Update email template with NFLPool language and remove default template

Update the picture used in the email templates
Add a picture to the email templates and give credit for the CC-By-SA licensed photo on the credits page
Fix an error in email_service, didn't need an import line there

Updating the submit picks process
Created a completed page (redirect there if you already have submitted picks or when done submitting). Trying to add code to check if you have already submitted picks - currently broken.

NFLPool will not let you submit picks more than once
Added a try / except on the query if the user_id has already submitted picks. If the query comes back none, proceed with picks. If the user_id of the user logged in is present in the picks table, redirects them to the completed page

Make the update schedule service work.
tl:dr: Updating the NFL schedule now works. So many things I had to fix. KeyErrors with bad JSON calls, bad POST call, list goes on.

Add super_user functionality to site.
Add su_email to secret_config. When creating an account, the account service will check against that email and make the user a superuser. Update controller to do a SQL query to only allow superusers to go to the admin pages.
Add su check to all admin pages

Add logging via logbook
And fixed an account query bug that drove me nuts for an hour.
Add Rollbar integration

Fix the reset password functionality.
I changed the routing from the default. 3 hours later of trouble shooting later and a half hour of my wife's time to find it.

Re-factor the submit picks process
Remove the try / except error handling and display the model if picks are equal to None rather than deal with a NoneType option. This will make my wife happy as she was telling me I was doing it wrong.

First pass at adding dynamic data to show completed picks
Skeleton is there, but the picks show as the INT and not the string due to the way the database stores picks. Need to join to the TeamInfo table.

Start complete rewrite of picks submission process
Start with the data model and add three new tables (DivisionInfo, ConferenceInfo, and PickTypes) Add services for all three and call the methods in the view model during the new install process

Fix database insert for PickTypes
Add service to controller and update method to fill the table

Continue to refactor the picks submission process
Add all new methods to insert each pick. Update the different type of picks in the PickTypes table. Fix the creation of the PlayerPicks table and rename the original to old
Almost forgot to add the db commit method for the picks. Almost.

Fix submit_picks check process if a user has already submitted picks.
Remove old picks.py - replaced by player_picks.py.

Fix new install process - wasn't adding data to the new tables
I thought this was working before I went to bed last night. Apparently not - now adding data to the 3 new tables.

Submit pick process is broken again.
When working to add a datetime check if the season has started, all users are coming back as picks completed even when the table is empty. Working on it.

Users can submit picks again - the check works.
The query needs to end with .first(). Aargh, how did that go away?!

Add datetime check to submit picks and update page templates
App will now check to see if the season has started before letting you submit picks. Added some fun gifs to the picks completed and too late pages
Change submit_picks to submit-picks and fix typo in completed
Remove print statements as testing is completed on submit-picks
Rename submit_picks to submit-picks

Re-factor all of the code to make lists for the picks page
Make it much more pythonic and reduce a lot of the methods by passing variables to the method rather than having a method for each individual query

Trying to get picks to display after being submitted
I hate committing broken code, but picks can't currently be displayed. The outer join isn't working and my SQL knowledge isn't enough.

Update list of needed modules and poke at showing picks
Viewing picks still isn't working.

The picks query now works! Remove old, unused files
The picks query now works and return an object with 41 rows. Remove old files in preparation for deployement.

The picks return query really works this time.
It now shows all of the columns because I'm dumb and forgot put them in the query.
Turn SQL echo off
Remove unused images and add favicon
Really add favicon this time
Add submit picks link to account page
Trying to fix the fonts without any luck
Fix broken link to submit-picks in welcome email

Fix the fonts in the CSS
The CSS files were out of order...

Change account created date displayed in Account
Remove the full datetime string in favor of YEAR-MONTH-DAY

Fix crash in account date method that I just pushed
The query worked when there was only 1 account in the db and crashed if there were more than two people. Fixed

Add a page to view picks by seasons played
My wife coded it all. What took me days to try and figure out in Chameleon took her hours.
Update view picks page to display the season in the title

Update account index page and footer
Remove the "coming soon" to view your picks as it is now fully working. Add link to about page in footer.

Start to add data pull from MSF API for weekly stats
Fix bug in playerpicks not showing DT as a choice in picks; add methods to get individual stats for API 1.0 (2016) and API 1.1 (2017 and beyond); update database tables to correctly store weekly stats

Pull all weekly stat categories from MySportsFeeds
Pull all individual and team stat categories from MySportsFeeds including a check for 2016 season using the 1.0 API or 2017 and later using the 1.1 API

Pull all team stats with a post via an admin page
All team and player stats are working. The team stat pull is ugly, but it works. Need some code cleanup and need to correctly calculate the week for the 2017 season and beyond.

Add method to calculate the season week for importing stats
If only I had a way to test this. Crossing my fingers it doesn't bomb in week 2.
Make the week calculation an integer and not a float
